<h2>Food assistance</h2>
<p>WFP is using trucks, tractors and helicopters in order to get food, shelter and other relief items to families in priority areas. The Government is providing food assistance in areas within the Kathmandu Valley&nbsp;while WFP is concentrating efforts outside the Valley, including remote mountain regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>WFP has distributed&nbsp;food to nearly two million people in seven districts.&nbsp;In other earthquake-affected areas, where household food stocks have been partially lost and where markets are partially functioning and recovering rapidly, WFP is providing survivors with cash so they can buy food locally, which revitalises markets. Also, WFP&#39;s emergency response includes cash-for-work so that critical community infrastructure is cleared of rubble.</p>
<h3>Related Information</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.wfp.org/stories/faqs-food-quality-and-safety-nepal">FAQs on food quality and safety in Nepal</a></li>
</ul>
<h2>Logistics</h2>
<p><aside class="media-small">
  <div class="media-img">
	<script src="//content.jwplatform.com/players/XnR5YJI9-D74JXXsN.js"></script>  </div>
	<div class="media-content">
	  	<h4 class="title">WFP Initiates Rapid Assessment As Second Quake Hits Nepal</h4>
				<p>Within hours of the second massive quake that struck Nepal on 12 May, WFP teams on the ground carried out an aerial assessment mission flying by helicopter to the affected area and speaking to local officials. <a href="https://www.wfp.org/node/647056">Text transcript of this video</a></p>
		</div>
</aside></p>
<p>WFP teams specialising in <a href="https://www.wfp.org/logistics">logistics</a> and <a href="https://www.wfp.org/our-work/emergencies">emergency response</a> are working hard to overcome immense challenges to reach remote villages. WFP is also coordinating the logistics needs of all UN agencies and Non-Government Organisations, through what is known as the Logistics Cluster, so that the wider response can be as efficient as possible.&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Impact</h2>
<p>WFP&rsquo;s team is working out of the <a href="http://www.wfp.org/news/news-release/nepal-opens-first-humanitarian-staging-area-built-government-uk-aid-support">Humanitarian Staging Area (HSA)</a>, which is a relief dispatch hub at Tribhuvan International Airport in Kathmandu. The HSA is a part of WFP&rsquo;s emergency preparedness work in Nepal. It includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>power</li>
<li>communications facilities</li>
<li>storage space</li>
<li>office buildings</li>
</ul>
<p>Additionally, WFP is providing common services for the entire humanitarian community, including storage facilities&nbsp;and is&nbsp;supporting the transportation of relief items that go beyond just food.&nbsp;</p>
